.\" Man page for lmm purge
.TH LMM-PURGE 1 "2026-01-29" "lmm" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lmm purge \- Remove all deployed mods from game directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lmm purge
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Remove all deployed mod files from the game directory for the given game and
profile. Mod records and cached files are preserved by default; use
\fB--uninstall\fR to also remove mod records from the database. Use
\fB--yes\fR to skip the confirmation prompt.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-game\fR=ID
Game ID (required unless default is set).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-profile\fR=NAME
Profile to purge (default: default).
.TP
.B \-\-uninstall
Also remove mod records (like uninstalling each mod).
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Skip confirmation prompt.
.TP
.B \-\-force
Continue even if hooks fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lmm (1),
.BR lmm-deploy (1),
.BR lmm-profile (1).
